{
  "texts": [
    "In the case of FM, SAC might demonstrate a slightly more stable transient behaviour attributed to the fact that the quantile regression process in TQC introduced complexity to the optimisation process.",
    "Both controllers achieved an identical level of drag reduction in the FM case.However, in the context of the PM cases, it is observed that TQC outperforms SAC in drag reduction with both static and dynamic feedback controllers.",
    "For static feedback control, TQC achieved an average drag reduction η = 56.00 %, compared to the η = 46.31 % reduction achieved by SAC.",
    "The performance under dynamic feedback control conditions is more compelling, where TQC fully reduced the drag, achieving η = 97.00 % of drag reduction, reverting it to a near-base-flow scenario.",
    "In contrast, SAC managed to achieve average drag reduction η = 96.52 %.The fundamental mechanism for updating Q-functions in RL involves selecting the maximum expected Q-functions among possible future actions."
  ]
}